        "padding_bottom_mobile": 40,
        "margin_top_mobile": 0,
        "margin_bottom_mobile": 0,
        "top_text": "Clinically Proven Remineralizing Ingredients",
        "main_headline": "Introducing Dr.Jen’s 10% nano Hydroxyapatite Toothpaste using clean ingredients and 10% nano-hydroxyapatite.",
        "dekstop_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_8_2.png",
        "img_card_link": "",
        "card_top_text": "",
        "card_headline": "",
        "card_desc": "<p>Since the introduction of nHAp into oral care products in 1980, there have been numerous peer-group clinical studies supporting nHAp as an effective remineralizing ingredient for toothpaste. Not only is nHAp efficient at remineralizing enamel, attaches to the plaque for easier removal during the brushing process,  manages hypersensitivity. In this side chart, the below study shows nHAp’s effect on enamel microhardness to be as effective as fluoride when applied to the enamel under cyclical conditions of pH, by a microhardness test, on cross sections (CSMH) and on surfaces through polarized light microscopy (PLM).</p>",
        "mobile_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_8_2.png",
        "card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4252862/\" title=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4252862/\">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4252862/</a></p>",
        "card_bottom_text": ""
      }
    },
