        "main_headline": "",
        "dekstop_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_11_1.png",
        "img_card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8233401/ \" title=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8233401/ \">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8233401/ </a></p>",
        "card_top_text": "",
        "card_headline": "Nano-hydroxyapatite +  Air sensitivity relief",
        "card_desc": "<p>The objective of this study was to investigate and compare the effectiveness of several toothpastes containing nano hydroxyapatite nHAP to relieve dentin hypersensitivity (DHS) with that of a commercial desensitizing dentifrice containing calcium sodium phosphosilicate (CSPS). Within the limits of this study, it can be concluded that toothpaste containing nano-HAP alone (10 or 15% nano-HAP) or supplemented with KNO3 (10%nano-HAKN) was effective in relieving DHS symptoms when used at least twice daily.</p>",
        "mobile_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_11_1.png",
        "card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8233401/ \" title=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8233401/ \">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8233401/ </a></p>",
        "card_bottom_text": "<p>Clinical efficacy of nanohydroxyapatite-containing toothpaste at relieving dentin hypersensitivity: an 8 weeks randomized control trial</p>"
      }
    },
