        "dekstop_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_13.png",
        "img_card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4232036/\" title=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4232036/\">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/ PMC4232036/</a></p>",
        "card_top_text": "",
        "card_headline": "Xylitol‐ containing products for preventing dental caries in children and adults",
        "card_desc": "<p>Xylitol is a natural sweetener that can prevent dental caries in both children and adults. It inhibits the growth of harmful bacteria in the mouth, reduces plaque formation, and promotes the remineralization of tooth enamel, thus preventing cavities. Xylitol, a natural sweetener found in fruits and vegetables, has been shown to prevent tooth decay by inhibiting harmful bacteria growth, reducing plaque formation, and promoting remineralization of tooth enamel. Toothpastes containing xylitol are better at preventing cavities due to their ability to maintain a neutral pH level in the mouth and inhibit acid production. Regular use of xylitol toothpaste can lead to a significant reduction in dental caries in both children and adults.</p>",
        "mobile_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_13.png",
        "card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4232036/\" title=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4232036/\">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/ PMC4232036/</a></p>",
        "card_bottom_text": "<p>In addition to using proper levels of nHAp for remineralizing, Dr. Jen’s toothpaste contains proper levels of xylitol to improve the oral micro-biome.</p>"
      }
    },
