        "dekstop_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_14_1.png",
        "img_card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24966732/#:~:text=Conclusion%3A%20 Peppermint%2C%20tea%20tree%20and,antiseptic%20solution%20against%20 oral%20pathogensinhibit acid production.\" title=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24966732/#:~:text=Conclusion%3A%20 Peppermint%2C%20tea%20tree%20and,antiseptic%20solution%20against%20 oral%20pathogensinhibit acid production.\">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24966732/#:~:text=Conclusion%3A%20 Peppermint%2C%20tea%20tree%20and,antiseptic%20solution%20against%20 oral%20pathogensinhibit acid production.</a></p>",
        "card_top_text": "",
        "card_headline": "Peppermint Oil",
        "card_desc": "<p>Replacing petroleum-based synthetic “Flavor” found in “Big Box” brands, Dr. Jen’s selected clinically proven essential oils to help manage halitosis and fight gingivitis. Dr. Jen’s proprietary blend of essential oils which include Peppermint, Spearmint, Black Cherry, and Papaya not only tastes great, but they also offer oral health benefits. Peppermint oil can act as an effective antiseptic solution against oral pathogens.<br/><br/>In some studies, peppermint oil reduced cavities better than some mouthwash chemicals like chlorhexidine. Peppermint oil makes the mouth feel fresh and of course, makes the formula taste good. Peppermint oil can also increase salivation.</p>",
        "mobile_image": "shopify://shop_images/image_14_1.png",
        "card_link": "<p><a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24966732/#:~:text=Conclusion%3A%20 Peppermint%2C%20tea%20tree%20and,antiseptic%20solution%20against%20 oral%20pathogensinhibit acid production.\" title=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24966732/#:~:text=Conclusion%3A%20 Peppermint%2C%20tea%20tree%20and,antiseptic%20solution%20against%20 oral%20pathogensinhibit acid production.\">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24966732/#:~:text=Conclusion%3A%20 Peppermint%2C%20tea%20tree%20and,antiseptic%20solution%20against%20 oral%20pathogensinhibit acid production.</a></p>",
        "card_bottom_text": "<p>Black Cherry and Papaya extracts contain antioxidants and anti-inflammatory benefits</p>"
      }
